      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together red chilli powder, brown sugar, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Rub the spice mixture all over the pork tenderloin.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together pickle juice and olive oil.",
    "Brush the pork tenderloin with the pickle juice mixture.",
    "Grill the pork for 10-12 minutes per side, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 145°F.",
    "Transfer the pork to a plate and let it rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve.",
    "Note: this recipe is for refrigerator pickling/preserving only — store in the refrigerator and consume within 1 week. Do not water-bath can without an acid (vinegar or lemon juice)."
